&nbsp;Struggle veteran Ahmed Kathrada has died his foundation said on Tuesday morning. He was 87 years old. &nbsp;In a tweet at 5.43am the foundation said: &#8220;Ahmed #Kathrada has passed on. Details to follow.&#8221; Kathrada had been ill for the last month with his condition deteriorating in the last 24 hours. He was taken in for surgery for surgery linked to blog clotting on the brain.The Ahmed Kathrada Foundation s Director Neeshan Balton said that the veteran had experienced several post-operation complications rendering his condition serious . Kathrada has contracted pneumonia which has affected both his lungs Balton said. Despite appropriate medical care his condition is deteriorating. He is currently comfortable. There was an immediate outpouring of grief on the social media platform.This is a developing story. Share this story: Click to share on Twitter (Opens in new window) Click to share on Facebook (Opens in new window) Click to share on LinkedIn (Opens in new window) Click to share on Tumblr (Opens in new window) Click to share on Google+ (Opens in new window) Click to share on WhatsApp (Opens in new window) Click to share on Pinterest (Opens in new window) Click to share on Reddit (Opens in new window) Click to email this to a friend (Opens in new window) Click to print (Opens in new window) Recommended Kathrada in a serious condition Kathrada still recovering in hospital after brain surgery Kathrada Foundation compares racist social media posts to Minstrels woes Tackle racism meaningfully to build nation